  "text": "The GUSTO I trial showed that among infarction patients with successful thrombolysis, 17% had progressive LV enlargement above 40 ml/m 2 . Mortality at one year was 16% among those with LVESVI 40 to 50 ml/m 2 , 21% with LVESVI 50 to 60 ml/m 2 and 33% when LVESVI >60 ml/m 2 [CITATION_1] .",
